JSON format rules

-> must start with "{"

-> key must be in doublequotes("")

-> values can be string , num , Boolean , array , obj , null

-> data are separated by comma


extensible markup language -- > it is a structured way of storing the data using tags(xml)

-> xml can create thier own tags eg: <name>Surya</name>

-> every xml file start with a single root element that wraps all data eg: <it>
                                                                            <stud>
                                                                             <stud1>Sharan</stud1>
                                                                             <stud2>Sharif</stud2>
                                                                             <stud3>Guru</stud3>
                                                                            </stud>
                                                                           </it>

TOMCAT

-> IT IS A webserver + java servlet container that runs java web application

-> it accepts http requests 

-> runs your java code

-> sent that http response

WHY TOMCAT?

-> broweser speak http

-> java application speak java code

-> Tomcat acts like a translator

-> coverts http into java calls

-> Tom cat is the middle man that connects web request with java programs


ARCHITECTURE

-> catelina 

-> coyota

-> jasper (to convert .jsp file to java )


BIN

-> start & stop

CONF

-> configure files

LIB

-> contain java files

LOG

-> it stores the error that occurs in the system

TEMP

-> temporary storage

WEBAPPS

-> here is where we should do  all our coding and application (like reactapp folder)(deployment folder)

